AMOYs were resting during much of the survey. However, a fast-moving pilot boat pushed a big wake on the shoreline, causing the shorebirds to flush and/or shift positions along the beach; most returned. Towards the end of the survey, an ATV patrolling the beach area, caused the shorebirds to flush; most AMOY departed.
